        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 9:34PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 934 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 15
miles northwest of Abbeville, or near Lake Secession, moving
northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Due West, Iva, Lake Secession, Starr, Lowndesville, Russell State
Park, Lake Russell, Belton, Antreville, and Nuberg.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
